This paper proposes a method for learning interpretable convolutional filters in a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) for object classification. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the learning process of the CNN, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper does not require additional annotations for supervision, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the semantic meaning of the interpretable filters, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the logic encoded in the CNN, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
